T1  - Confidence Interval Estimation for the Variance Parameter of Stationary Processes
AU  - Chen, Bor-Chung
AU  - Sargent, Robert G.
Y1  - 1990/02/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.36.2.200
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.36.2.200
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 200
EP  - 211
VL  - 36
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Asymptotic confidence interval estimators of the variance parameter σ2 = limn ? ∞ n Var((1/n) ?ni = 1 Xi) are described in this paper for observations X1, X2,?,Xn from a strictly stationary phi-mixing stochastic process. They are based on asymptotic properties of the standardized time series of observations from the process. The new point and interval estimators for the variance parameter are compared to the classical batch means estimator. The results show that the new estimators have asymptotic properties that clearly dominate the classical estimator. Also, asymptotic confidence interval estimators for the ratio of two variance parameters representing two independent processes are discussed.
AB  - Asymptotic confidence interval estimators of the variance parameter σ2 = limn ? ∞ n Var((1/n) ?ni = 1 Xi) are described in this paper for observations X1, X2,?,Xn from a strictly stationary phi-mixing stochastic process. They are based on asymptotic properties of the standardized time series of observations from the process. The new point and interval estimators for the variance parameter are compared to the classical batch means estimator. The results show that the new estimators have asymptotic properties that clearly dominate the classical estimator. Also, asymptotic confidence interval estimators for the ratio of two variance parameters representing two independent processes are discussed.
